HEADWORD: Theatricals
<hw>The*at"ric*als</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <def>Dramatic
performances; especially, those produced by amateurs.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Such fashionable cant terms as ⟦lsquo⟧<qex>theatricals</qex>,' and
⟦lsquo⟧musicals,' invented by the flippant Topham, still survive among
his confraternity of frivolity.</q> <rj><qau>I. Disraeli.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

